{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A file placed inside a subdirectory of the watched root is processed, not only files placed directly in the root directory.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary is real filesystem watch behavior across directory hierarchy (watcher config + OS event delivery). MOCK-MISS: a unit test of path logic cannot prove subdirectory events are emitted. REAL-INFRA/MOCK-HIDE: mocked watcher events could always pass while real recursive watching is misconfigured. No LLM dependency, no multi-step agent pipeline.","test_description":"Start the real daemon against a temporary watched root and output dir. Create a nested subdirectory under the watched root, then write a new file inside it. Assert exactly one transformed output artifact appears for that nested file path within timeout.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.13,"System":0.86,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The deduplication logic correctly discards a second processing request for the same file path within a configurable time window.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Behavior is explicitly deduplication logic at one object/function boundary. MOCK-MISS: no required module handoff to reproduce core failure. REAL-INFRA: no OS/network/subprocess required. Rejection-gate: Integration/System were considered and rejected because behavior text is about the dedupe rule itself, not watcher/event infrastructure.","test_description":"Instantiate the deduper with a configurable window and a controllable clock. Submit the same file path twice within the window and assert first returns accepted, second returns discarded; advance clock past window and assert a new request is accepted.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.78,"Integration":0.19,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When