erently OS watcher behavior. Integration-brake: (a) no real OS/network/subprocess is strictly required if arrivals and timestamps are provided in-process; (b) no AI output dependency; (c) no multi-agentic chain; (d) no LLM-involved orchestration. Rejection-gate: System was considered and rejected because behavior text specifies ordering rule by timestamps, not OS event-delivery correctness.","test_description":"Wire ingest, metadata, and queue modules together in-process. Inject multiple arrival requests with controlled creation timestamps (including close/equal times) and assert processing order follows ascending creation timestamp regardless of arrival call order.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"A file that is still being written to when the arrival event fires is not picked up for processing until writing is complete.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary is real write-in-progress behavior and event timing (partial writes, file stability checks) at OS/filesystem level. MOCK-HIDE: mocked file completion or atomic writes can hide partial-read races. No LLM or workflow dependency.","test_description":"Run daemon on a real temp watched directory. Start writing a large file in chunks with delays so arrival event fires before final chunk. Assert daemon does not process during partial-write period and processes only after writer closes/completes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.9,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
